show_title: GM Farcaster ep267 Wednesday July 16, 2025 with guest cohost @erica /uno
text:
The experiment didn't work out. 

I haven't been regular about recording updates and this has been frustrating for devs. My apologies for that, and we're going to do better going forward. 

Dev calls will happen (again) every other Thursday at 10am PT. The format remains the same: a quick overview from me and others on the team with time for open Q&A. Suggestions to improve this format are welcome. 

The next call will be on Thursday the 17th of July @ 10am PT. 

Please add this shared calendar if you want to join the dev calls

https://calendar.google.com/calendar/u/0?cid=NjA5ZWM4Y2IwMmZiMWM2ZDYyMTkzNWM1YWNkZTRlNWExN2YxOWQ2NDU3NTA3MjQwMTk3YmJlZGFjYTQ3MjZlOEBncm91cC5jYWxlbmRhci5nb29nbGUuY29t

cast.text:
We're changing the format of Farcaster Dev Calls. 

- 5m weekly videos summarizing the major changes. 
- 1h q&a session every month for feedback.
- impromtu dev calls if there are major discussion points in between. 

We're going to try this for two months and revert back the old format if people don't like this.

show_title: GM Farcaster ep267 Wednesday July 16, 2025 with guest cohost @erica /uno
text:
Cura is making it easy to discover channels!

now you can surface the best content across topics you love, powered by farcaster channels. try the app 👇 

why?
- some of the best content about your fav topic or interest lives in channels.
- most new users land on farcaster, stumble upon channels and aren’t sure what to do next. we want to make it easy for users to discover channels they vibe with
- channels with quality conversations want these to be persistent, not lost in an ephemeral feed
- power users want to double click on certain topics and don't know which channels have high signal users and content

https://cura.network/?t=topics

html.ogDescription: Discover channels by topics and trending content in channels

show_title: GM Farcaster ep267 Wednesday July 16, 2025 with guest cohost @erica /uno
text:
another look at what happens when you don't put the spam filter* on

37+ one word replies to a single cast that continued to come in while recording

with more bots/agents coming online, spam filters/affinity algorithms (or whatever you choose to call them) will become even more important to the end user experience

it will take continuous tinkering, learning, experimenting to get them right and keep them efficient at doing what they're supposed to do - sorting out content that is not relevant to you

cast.text:
We’re testing notification filters this week. Notifications won’t be pushed if our affinity prediction is too low.

e.g. you don’t know the user, the user is likely spammy, their overall engagement is super asymmetrical.

For context, this is what life is like without algorithms.
